Online payment platform 3G Direct Pay has rebranded to Direct Pay Online Group following a significant new investment by private equity firm Apis Growth Fund.Direct Pay, which serves more than 5,000 merchants in the region seeks to tap into the new trend of online shopping to grow threefold by 2020.The new investor has injected Sh1 billion into the business, which will enable Direct Pay Online Group to expand the business to more than 10 countries in East, West and Southern Africa in the next one year."The shift of consumers from physical to digital channels is one of the most significant trends in our markets, and we believe online payments are at the centre of these developments," Apis co-founder and managing partner Matteo Stefan said.